-- 
BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Current Account, Weekly CPI, Oil Seminar in Rio

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-05-25T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/brazil-daybook-current-account-weekly-cpi-oil-seminar-in-rio.html
Brazil  will post a current account
deficit of $4.85 billion for the month of April, according to
the average estimate in a Bloomberg survey of 18 economists. The
deficit in March was $5.68 billion. The central bank releases
new figures at 10:30 a.m. local time and the bank’s economic
department head, Tulio Maciel, speaks to reporters about the
numbers at 11 a.m.  GOVERNMENT:
*President  Dilma Rousseff  has internal meetings.
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega has internal meetings in the
morning and a meeting with labor unions at 6 p.m.
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini has meetings in
Brasilia.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Officials from Petrobras, Pemex, Statoil, Total, Shell,
Petroperu, HRT, Statoil  Colombia ’s ANH and Brazil’s ANP are
scheduled to speak at the 17th Latin Oil week conference in Rio
de Janeiro.
*Executives of insurance companies, including  Munich Re ’s
Nikolaus von Bomhard, Tokio Marine & Nichido Fire Insurance
Co.’s Kunio Ishiara, and Sul America Seguros’s Patrick de
Larragoiti Lucas participate in conference in Rio de Janeiro.
*Light SA to hold meeting with investors in Sao Paulo at 6 p.m.  ECONOMY:
*Fipe weekly  consumer price index  at 5 a.m.
*FGV consumer confidence at 8 a.m.
*Current account at 10:30 a.m.
*Foreign direct investment at 10:30 a.m.
*Central government budget balance  EQUITIES:
*JBS (JBSS3 BZ) unit takes 7-Year, $475 million loan. *Petrobras
(PETR4 BZ) says no date yet for new business plan. *Units of
Telemar (TLMP3 BZ) surged the most in two years in Sao Paulo
after the parent company said it will merge them into one entity
that will be Brazil’s largest fixed-line telephone service
provider.  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 1.6 percent to 63,336.75.
*The real gained 0.6 percent to 1.6241 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
